			</contentSection><contentSection id="3">
				<title>
					Home Base
				</title>
				<navigationLabel>
					Home Base
				</navigationLabel>
				<contentItems>
					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							There are various groups of termites &#8211; wood, subterranean, tube-building, and mound-building &#8211; that live all over the world in dark, damp environments where they are not exposed to air. Mound termites build huge nests that can grow to more than 21 feet (6 meters) tall, while subterranean termite colonies build their nests under tree stumps or soil and wood termites excavate holes in trees or man-made structures.
						</text>
